                            <comment id="16619071" author="cziegeler" created="Tue, 18 Sep 2018 12:58:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For some reason the update algorithm always assumed that the update is simply supplying the same configuration&lt;br/&gt;
This is fixed now in rev 1841224&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16621506" author="cziegeler" created="Thu, 20 Sep 2018 04:48:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jalbert&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jalbert&quot;&gt;jalbert&lt;/a&gt; You don&apos;t need &quot;:configurator:policy&quot; - the policy is only needed when someone changed the configuration manually between your bundle updates&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
